// Terminal Manager
// Manages tmux terminal sessions: storage I/O, tmux lifecycle, and reconciliation with stored state.

Session metadata is stored at .collab/sessions/{session}/terminal-sessions.json (new) or
.collab/{session}/terminal-sessions.json (legacy).
A singleton instance (terminalManager) is exported for convenience.

FUNCTION getStoragePath(project, session) -> string
  Private. Check new location first; if it or its parent directory exists, return it.
  Otherwise check old location. Default to new location.

---

FUNCTION readSessions(project, session) -> TerminalSessionsState
  CALLS: getStoragePath (terminal-manager)
  Read and parse the JSON file at the storage path.
  IF file does not exist or read fails, return an empty sessions state with a fresh timestamp.

---

FUNCTION writeSessions(project, session, state) -> void
  CALLS: getStoragePath (terminal-manager)
  Create the directory if needed. Update state.lastModified to now. Write JSON to disk.

---

FUNCTION generateTmuxSessionName(collabSession) -> string
  Extract the last segment of the collabSession name (split by ':' or '/').
  Sanitize to lowercase alphanumeric only, truncate to 20 chars.
  Append a 4-character random hex suffix.
  Return "mc-{sanitized}-{suffix}".

---

FUNCTION createTmuxSession(tmuxSessionName, cwd) -> void
  Run tmux new-session -d with optional -c for working directory.
  Enable mouse mode on the new session.
  Attempt to unbind split keys (Ctrl+B % and Ctrl+B "); failures are non-fatal.
  IF a "duplicate session" error occurs, treat as success: apply mouse mode and attempt key unbinds.
  Other errors are rethrown.

---

FUNCTION killTmuxSession(tmuxSessionName) -> void
  Run tmux kill-session. IF the session does not exist ("no session" error), treat as success.
  Other errors are rethrown.

---

FUNCTION listActiveTmuxSessions(prefix) -> string[]
  Run tmux list-sessions and parse the output.
  Filter to session names starting with the given prefix.
  Return empty array if tmux is not running.

---

FUNCTION reconcileSessions(project, session) -> void
  CALLS: readSessions (terminal-manager), listActiveTmuxSessions (terminal-manager),
         killTmuxSession (terminal-manager), writeSessions (terminal-manager)
  Read stored sessions and list active tmux sessions with the "mc-{session}-" prefix.
  Remove stored entries whose tmux sessions are no longer active (orphaned records).
  Kill active tmux sessions that have no corresponding stored entry (orphaned tmux sessions).
  Write the cleaned state and log a reconciliation summary.
